docs.description: You can employ webhooks to notify external systems whenever there are additions, updates, or removals of rows within NocoDB. NocoDB also offers webhooks for bulk endpoints for creating, updating, or deleting multiple records simultaneously.

docs.title: Attachment
docs.description: Attachment fields allow you to upload files to your records. You can upload any file type, and the file will be linked to the record. You can also upload multiple files to a single Attachment field record.

docs.title: Barcode
docs.description: Barcode is a custom field type that allows you to generate a barcode from a string value. This is useful for generating barcodes for things like URLs, phone numbers, or other data that can be represented as a string.

docs.title: Checkbox
docs.description: The checkbox field type is used to store boolean values. It can be used to store a simple yes/no value, or true/false, or any other boolean value.

docs.title: Geometry
docs.description: Create a geometry field

docs.title: JSON
docs.description: JSON is a custom field type that allows you to store JSON data in a field. Useful for storing data that can be represented as a JSON object, like API Response, or a set of key-value pairs.

docs.title: QR code
docs.description: QR code is a custom field type that allows you to generate a QR code from a string value. This is useful for generating QR codes for things like URLs, phone numbers, or other data that can be represented as a string.

docs.title: Date Time
docs.description: Date Time field type is used to store both date and time values in a single field.

docs.title: Duration
docs.description: Duration field type is used to store duration of time in seconds or minutes. Different formats are supported by NocoDB, as detailed in the table below.

docs.title: Time

docs.title: Links
docs.description: Links field type is used to establish relationship between tables & create links to other records.

docs.title: LookUp
docs.description: Lookup fields help bring additional field information from related table into the current table. This is useful when you want to display additional information about a record in a table. For example, if you have a table of Orders and a table of Customers, you can use a Lookup field to display the customer's name and address in the Orders table.

docs.title: Rollup
docs.description: Rollup fields are used to aggregate data from fields in the related table. Often used to calculate totals, averages, and other aggregate data.

docs.title: Currency
docs.description: Currency field type is used to store currency values. It is a numerical field with additional provision to set the currency symbol in display.

docs.title: Decimal
docs.description: Decimal field type is used to store decimal values. Use cases include storing salary, price, etc. NocoDB supports precision of upto 8 digits.

docs.title: Number
docs.description: Number field type is used to store numerical values. Use cases include storing age, salary, price, quantity, etc.

docs.title: Percent
docs.description: Percent field type is used to store percentage values. Use cases include storing discount, tax, etc.

docs.title: Multi Select
docs.description: Multi Select fields allow you to select multiple options from a list of options. The options can be defined in the field configuration.

docs.title: Single Select
docs.description: Single select fields allow you to select a single option from a list of options. The options can be defined in the field configuration.

docs.title: Email
docs.description: Email field is text based field custom-built for storing E-mail IDs. It is a special type of Single line text field with

docs.title: Long text
docs.description: Long Text field is text based field that allows text in multiple lines. It is useful for storing lengthy text like description, notes, etc.

docs.title: Phone Number
docs.description: Phone number field is text based field that allows you to store phone numbers. It also allows you to validate the phone number.

docs.title: Single line text
docs.description: Single line text field is a simple text based field. It can hold any text value. It is generally used for storing short text values like name, email, phone number, etc. For storing text values with multiple lines, use Long text field.

Let's dive in and unlock the potential of NocoDB for your data management needs.

docs.title: Download
docs.description: NocoDB offers users the ability to export data from the spreadsheet grid in a variety of formats. This feature is useful when working with large datasets and can be used in conjunction with the Filter and Sort feature to further refine your data.

docs.title: Filtering records
docs.description: Filters provide a powerful way to narrow down and organize your data according to your specific requirements. NocoDB supports nested filters, allowing you to select multiple columns and conditions for filtering. You can choose between and or or mode of operation to combine filters, and filtering also supports Lookup, Formula, and Nested Data.

docs.title: Grouping records
docs.description: Grouping records in NocoDB allows for efficient categorization of data into specific Groups and Subgroups. NocoDB supports three levels of record segregation, providing a powerful organizational tool.

docs.title: Table operations overview
docs.description: Learn how to work with filters, sort, group by, and more in NocoDB.

frontMatter.title: Table operations overview
frontMatter.description: Learn how to work with filters, sort, group by, and more in NocoDB.

docs.title: Row height
docs.description: NocoDB offers users the flexibility to adjust the display height of records within the spreadsheet grid to four distinct levels: Short (the default setting), Medium, Tall, and Extra. This feature proves valuable when working with extensive text columns and multi-select fields, as it enables users to present a greater amount of content within each cell.

docs.title: Search
docs.description: NocoDB offers a quick search feature that allows you to search for records by field from the toolbar menu. This feature is useful when working with large datasets and can be used in conjunction with the Filter feature to further refine your search results.

docs.title: Sorting records
docs.description: Sorting enables you to arrange your data alphabetically (A → Z) or (Z → A) for text based types and in ascending or descending order for numerical types. NocoDB supports nested sorting, allowing you to select fields and the order in which to apply nested sorting.

docs.title: Gallery
docs.description: Gallery View allows you to display images as thumbnails with other fields just like a gallery. This view type is ideal for viewing images in a gallery-like interface. Like in Gallery, you can also perform various operations on the gallery view, such as sorting, filtering, grouping, and searching. You can also export the data in the gallery view to CSV or Excel format. This section will cover all the operations that can be performed on the gallery view.

docs.title: Grid
docs.description: Grid View, as a default type of view, allows you to display your data in a spreadsheet-like interface using rows and columns. Rows are as referred to as records and columns as fields in NocoDB.
